	    <!--
	<Image Grid.Row="1" Width="250" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" Grid.RowSpan="6" Stretch="Uniform" HorizontalAlignment="Center" VerticalAlignment="Center" Source="{Binding Assets[ts_banner]}"/>
	-->
    <TextBlock Grid.Row="9" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" FontSize="{StaticResource Font.Size.Header}" TextWrapping="Wrap">		TOP SECRET
		<LineBreak/>
		<LineBreak/>
		1. (TS) THIS IS AN EXECUTE ORDER BY AUTHORITY AND DIRECTION OF THE SECRETARY OF DEFENSE.
		<LineBreak/>
		<LineBreak/>
		2. (TS) SITUATION: FOLLOWING HOSTILE ACTION BY LIBYAN FORCES DURING OUR FREEDOM OF NAVIGATION OPERATIONS (AIR AND SURFACE) IN THE GULF OF SIDRA SOUTH OF 32-30N, JCS HAS AUTHORIZED OPERATION PRAIRIE FIRE.
		<LineBreak/>
		<LineBreak/>
		2. (TS) MISSION: TF 60 WILL CONDUCT STRIKES AGAINST THE PRIORITY TARGETS PLANNED UNDER PRAIRIE FIRE UPON RECEIPT OF THIS EXECUTE ORDER.
		<LineBreak/>
		<LineBreak/>
		3. (TS) EXECUTION: SARATOGA CVBG (TG 60.2) AIRWING UNITS WILL DESTROY LIBYAN SA-5 SAM BATTERY AT SIRTE, AND PROVIDE CAP AND SUCAP FOR TICONDEROGA SAG. TICONDEROGA SAG (TG 60.5) WILL COMMENCE TRANSIT THROUGH GULF OF SIDRA THEN TAKE UNDER FIRE AND DESTROY ANY HOSTILE LIBYAN NAVAL COUNTERATTACK.
		<LineBreak/>
		<LineBreak/>
		4. (TS) WARNING: LIBYAN AIR FORCE OUT OF TRIPOLI MAY SORTIE IN SUPPORT OF NAVAL FORCES.
		<LineBreak/>
		<LineBreak/>
		5. (TS) ROE REMAINS AS STATED. DESTROY ALL HOSTILE FORCES. GOOD LUCK AND GOOD HUNTING. COMSIXTHFLT SENDS.
		<LineBreak/>
		<LineBreak/>
		TOP SECRET
		<LineBreak/>
		DECL OADR BT
